HEADWORD: Syncretistic
<hw>Syn`cre*tis"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Pertaining to, or characterized by, syncretism; <as>as, a
<ex>syncretistic</ex> mixture of the service of Jehovah and the worship
of idols</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to Syncretists.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Syncrisis</ent>⟦br⟧
